{
  "text": "Musculoskeletal disorders. Four systematic reviews investigated the association between sedentary behavior and musculoskeletal disorders. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] In children, there is insufficient evidence on the association between exposure to screen-based sedentary behavior and musculoskeletal [CITATION_5] and low back pain. [CITATION_6] Similarly, for adults, there is limited evidence on the association between sedentary behavior (occupational sitting; computer use; sedentary behavior and prolonged sitting-time during leisure; and total sitting time) and low back pain, neck pain, shoulder pain, hand pain and arm pain. [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] .",
